The paper discusses the use of deep representation learning algorithms for goal exploration in complex environments, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given that the paper focuses on the use of deep representation learning algorithms, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, since the paper also discusses the application of these algorithms to real-world robots, cs.RO is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of disentangled representations, which is a topic that falls under cs.CV and cs.SY. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely for this paper.
